Jacobi Prior for Supervised Learning

SDSS Star Classification: Exploratory Data Analysis

Sourish Das and Shouvik Sardar

Here we are running an exploratory data analysis (EDA) of SDSS star dataset. We will run the EDA only on the training dataset.

Read the data

df=read.csv(file="SDSS_star_classification.csv",head=T)

Processing to create indicator variable (aka., one-hot encoding) for different classes

df$GALAXY=rep(0,nrow(df))
df$GALAXY[df$class=="GALAXY"]<-1
df$STAR=rep(0,nrow(df))
df$STAR[df$class=="STAR"]<-1
df$QSO=rep(0,nrow(df))
df$QSO[df$class=="QSO"]<-1

Split the data into train and test

n = nrow(df)
m = floor(n*0.7)
RNGkind(sample.kind = "Rounding")
set.seed(7599)
id_train=sort(sample(1:n,m,replace = F))

df.train = df[id_train,]
df.test  = df[-id_train,]

Outlier in the training dataset

df.train[df.train$g<0,]
##             obj_ID    alpha      delta     u     g       r        i     z
## 79544 1.237649e+18 224.0065 -0.6243039 -9999 -9999 18.1656 18.01675 -9999
##       run_ID rerun_ID cam_col field_ID  spec_obj_ID class plate   MJD fiber_ID
## 79544    752      301       2      537 3.731277e+18  STAR  3314 54970      162
##       GALAXY STAR QSO
## 79544      0    1   0

Dropping this one point from the data. Looks like it is a missing value - out of 100,000 values.

df.train<-df.train[df.train$g>0,]

Visualisation

tabl = table(df.train$class)
tabl
## 
## GALAXY    QSO   STAR 
##  41742  13211  15046
prop.table(tabl)
## 
##    GALAXY       QSO      STAR 
## 0.5963228 0.1887313 0.2149459
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
pie(tabl,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))
barplot(tabl,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"),horiz=T)

boxplot(alpha~class,data=df.train,pch=20
        ,ylab="alpha: Right Ascension angle",xlab=""
        ,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))

boxplot(delta~class,data=df.train,pch=20
        ,ylab="Delta : Declination angle",xlab=""
        ,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))

boxplot(u~class,data=df.train,pch=20
        ,ylab="Ultraviolet filter",xlab=""
        ,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))

boxplot(g~class,data=df.train,pch=20
        ,ylab="Gree filter",xlab=""
        ,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))

boxplot(r~class,data=df.train,pch=20
        ,ylab="Red filter",xlab=""
        ,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))

boxplot(i~class,data=df.train,pch=20
        ,ylab="Near Infrared filter",xlab=""
        ,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))

boxplot(z~class,data=df.train,pch=20
        ,ylab="Infrared filter",xlab=""
        ,col=c("orange","skyblue","lightgreen"))

hist(df.train$alpha,main="",xlab = "alpha"
     ,probability = T,col="snow2")

hist(df.train$delta,main="",xlab = "delta"
     ,probability = T,col="snow2")

hist(df.train$u,main="",xlab = "ultraviolet filter"
     ,probability = T,col="violetred")

hist(df.train$g,main="",xlab = "green filter"
     ,probability = T,col="green")

hist(df.train$r,main="",xlab = "red filter"
     ,probability = T,col="red")

hist(df.train$i,main="",xlab = "near infrared filter"
     ,probability = T,col="red3")

hist(df.train$z,main="",xlab = "infrared filter"
     ,probability = T,col="red4")

df.train$class_col<-NA
df.train$class_col[df.train$class=="GALAXY"]<-"orange"
df.train$class_col[df.train$class=="QSO"]<-"skyblue"
df.train$class_col[df.train$class=="STAR"]<-"lightgreen"

plot(df.train$i
     ,df.train$g
     ,col=df.train$class_col,pch=20
     ,xlab="Near Infrared Filter"
     ,ylab="Green Filter")

plot(df.train$z
     ,df.train$r
     ,col=df.train$class_col,pch=20
     ,xlab="Infrared Filter"
     ,ylab="Red Filter")

plot(df.train$u
